RACE.RACE_TEXT: Steve Sexton Mile S. - Grade3 LONE STAR PARK RACE 12 1M Dirt CR: 113. Stakes Purse 400000. (PLUS UP TO $15,000 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. No nomination fee. $2,000 to pass the entry box and an additional $2,000 to start. Supplemental nominations may be made at time of entry for $6,000 and shall include all fees. After payment of 1.5% of the total purse to all owners finishing sixth through last, 60% of the remaining purse shall be paid to the winning owner, 20% to second, 11% to third, 6% to fourth, and 3% to fifth. If less than five horses start, the remaining purse will be dis tributed to the winning owner. Starters to be named through the entry box by the usual time of closing. Weights: Three Year Old, 121 lbs. Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners of $90,000 at a mile or over in 2023 allowed 2 lbs.; Non-winners of $60,000 since Novembe r 29, 2022 allowed 4 lbs.; Non-winners of $30,000 in 2022-2023 allowed 6 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: FROSTED GRACE chased the pace while two wide down the backstretch and into the far turn, came out four wide to menace at the top of the lane then edged clear late to prove best in the end. TOUCHUPONASTAR vied for the while three wide, then dueled with inner rival at the top of the bend, shook clear to lead in the early stretch but could not go with Frosted Grace in the late stretch and was second best. KOKOKOMO was unhurried early while saving ground down the backstretch, then bid on the far turn, angled out seven to eight wide to close gap fast to just miss, too late. SONNEMAN saved ground down the backstretch, then bid while three wide on the far turn, rallied mildly in the late stretch and needed more in the end. MINE THAT STAR vied for the lead from the inside throughout the first three quarters then tired in the late stretch. SILVER PROSPECTOR chased the pace while three wide, then rallied on the far turn but did not fire in the stretch. ALLEGE chased the pace from the inside then flattened out in the final furlongs and needed more in the end. LOGICAL MYTH stalked the pace while two wide then moved up to duel with an inner rival throughout the bend was used up and tired in late stretch. ENDORSED chased the pace while four wide, then lost momentum throughout the far turn and stopped. HOLDEN THE LUTE was in a long drive to vie for the lead between rivals, then dropped back on the far turn and stopped.
